'''''Star Wars Insider'' 84''' was the 84th issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'', released on [[September 26]], [[2005]].

This issue was published with three different collector's covers: [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Bly/Legends|Bly]], Commander [[Gree (clone trooper)/Legends|Gree]], & a [[2nd Airborne Company/Legends|2nd Airborne Company]] trooper were all featured, each with their own cover.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]"
*"[[Skywalking]]: News from Around the Galaxy"
*"[[Jedi Library (department)|Jedi Library]]" &mdash; Collecting History: Two Books That Delve into ''Star Wars'' Lore {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Drawn by the Force]]" &mdash; [[Purge (comic book)|Wipe Them Out, All of Them]] {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]]}}
*"[[Set Piece|Technical Readout]]" &mdash; Geonosis Arena {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master]]" &mdash; A ''Star Wars'' Time Warp {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; Finding a Treasure In a Used Bookstore Bin {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Jabba's Collection]]" &mdash; Hasbro Battle Packs Hit the Front Lines {{C|by Brett Rector}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]" &mdash; Lights, Camera, Jedi: The Sets of Episode III {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 15
*"Emperor's Exhibit" {{C|by [[Matt Busch]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Guide to the Grand Army of the Republic]]" {{C|by [[Karen Traviss]] and [[Ryan Kaufman (real person)|Ryan Kaufman]], with illustrations by [[Chris Trevas]]}}
*:<small>Before they became the dreaded stormtroopers, they were an army of peacekeeping clone troopers. Find out everything you need to know about them in this highly detailed guide.</small>
*"[[The Art of Revenge of the Sith|The Art of ''Revenge of the Sith'']], Part Two" {{C|by [[Jonathan W. Rinzler]]}}
*:<small>In ''Insider''{{'s}} continued effort to unearth never-before-seen artwork from ''Revenge of the Sith'', we take you through a day in the life of the concept artists in ILM's art department.</small>
*"[[Lurking in the Shadows: The Creatures of Episode III]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>In addition to multiple Jedi, thousands of clone troopers, and an evil Sith Lord, ''Revenge of the Sith'' also features some fantastical creatures. Take a trip with us as we explore them in their natural habitats. Just be sure to keep your hands and feet in the hovercraft at all times to avoid any personal injury.</small>
*"[[HoloNet News (Insider)|HoloNetNews]]: [[Republic HoloNet News Special Inaugural Edition 16:5:241]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]] and [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*:<small>HoloNet Flash: The Jedi have been caught in an act of treason, and efforts to remove their presence from the galaxy are taking place. The new Galactic Empire, under the rule of Emperor Palpatine, is requesting that all citizens pledge their support to the new government and report any suspicious activities. Failure to comply will result in dire consequences for the offender. We now return you to your regularly scheduled programming.</small>
*"[[Posters of Episode IV: A New Hope|Posters of Episode IV: ''A New Hope'']]" {{C|by [[Pete Vilmur]]}}
*:<small>With ''[[The Star Wars Poster Book]]'' about to be unleashed to the public, we thought we'd put together a little feature to show you what you ''won't'' see within its pages, from the film that launched a cinematic renaissance.</small>

